{"@context":"http://iiif.io/api/presentation/3/context.json","id":"https://digbmc.github.io/pta-manifests/phan/phan-04253/manifest.json","type":"Manifest","label":{"none":["PHAN-04253"]},"metadata":[{"label":{"none":["Timestamp"]},"value":{"none":["0:42:53"]}},{"label":{"none":["Film"]},"value":{"none":["Phantom Thread"]}},{"label":{"none":["Creator"]},"value":{"none":["Paul Thomas Anderson"]}},{"label":{"none":["Distance"]},"value":{"none":["extreme close-up"]}},{"label":{"none":["Angle"]},"value":{"none":["eye-level"]}},{"label":{"none":["Location"]},"value":{"none":["interior"]}},{"label":{"none":["Movement"]},"value":{"none":["fixed"]}},{"label":{"none":["Composition"]},"value":{"none":["single shot"]}}],"summary":{"none":["A man looks out of a peephole."]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04253/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"homepage":[{"id":"PHAN-04253","type":"Text","format":"text/html","label":{"none":["Object homepage"]}}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04253/canvas/1","type":"Canvas","height":1080,"width":1920,"label":{"none":["PHAN-04253"]},"thumbnail":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04253/tiles/full/300,169/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":169,"width":300}],"items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04253/canvas/1/annopage-1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04253/canvas/1/annopage-1/anno-1","type":"Annotation","motivation":"painting","target":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04253/canvas/1","body":{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04253/tiles/full/1920,1080/0/default.jpg","type":"Image","format":"image/jpeg","height":1080,"width":1920,"service":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04253/tiles","type":"ImageService3","profile":"http://iiif.io/api/image/3/level0.json"}]}}]}],"annotations":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04253/canvas/1/page/p1","type":"AnnotationPage","items":[{"id":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04253/canvas/1/87846632-5057-4afa-8b73-af8aed67a851","type":"Annotation","motivation":"commenting","body":[{"created":"2026-06-30T19:34:36.115Z","creator":"g","purpose":"commenting","type":"TextualBody","format":"text/html","value":"<p>In one of <em>Phantom Thread</em>’s most bravura shots, one that likewise recalls the cinematography of PTA’s early films, the camera swerves to follow Reynolds to the peephole from the dressing room and, then, tracks his eye in an extreme close-up. On a key level, the film is about the artist’s (and male) gaze, how it watches and perceives its creations. In this case, Reynolds views Alma as someone (something) that he can craft and change through his art of dressmaking. There is, of course, a sexual undertone to all this gazing and peeping. Reynolds and Alma both appear excited as they flirt with each other through the peephole with knowing looks. This shot is a clear reference to <a target=\"_blank\" rel=\"noreferrer noopener\" class=\"Hyperlink SCXW140271666 BCX4\" href=\"https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=ghew-s2zPjE\"><u>Norman Bates spying on Marion Crane</u></a> in Alfred Hitchcock’s <em>Psycho </em>(1960) (Movaghati, “Bluebeard Meets Ivy,” 724).&nbsp;</p>"}],"target":{"type":"SpecificResource","source":"https://digitalscholarship.brynmawr.edu/pta/phan/phan-04253/canvas/1","selector":{"type":"FragmentSelector","conformsTo":"http://www.w3.org/TR/media-frags/","value":"xywh=pixel:218.35800807537015,141.39973082099604,966.4602960969044,590.4710632570659"}}}]}]}]}